    "section3Content": "You agree to:\n\n• Use the platform in accordance with its intended purpose.\n• Not attempt to bypass security measures.\n• Not use the service for unlawful purposes.\n• Respect the confidentiality of patient data.",
    "section4Title": "4. Data Protection",
    "section4Content": "The processing of personal data is governed by our Privacy Policy. Dokal is committed to complying with the GDPR and all applicable data protection regulations.",
    "section5Title": "5. Intellectual Property",
    "section5Content": "All elements of the Dokal platform (interface, code, logos, content) are protected by intellectual property rights. Any unauthorized reproduction, modification or use is strictly prohibited.",
    "section6Title": "6. Liability",
    "section6Content": "Dokal strives to ensure the availability and reliability of the service. However, Dokal shall not be liable for:\n\n• Service interruptions due to maintenance or technical reasons.\n• Indirect damages resulting from the use of the service.\n• Data loss in the event of force majeure.",
    "section7Title": "7. Termination",
    "section7Content": "You may terminate your account at any time from your profile settings. Dokal reserves the right to suspend or delete an account in the event of a breach of these Terms.",
    "section8Title": "8. Amendments",
    "section8Content": "Dokal reserves the right to amend these Terms at any time. You will be notified of any material changes. Continued use of the service constitutes acceptance of the amended Terms.",
    "section9Title": "9. Governing Law",
    "section9Content": "These Terms are governed by French law. Any dispute shall be submitted to the competent courts of Paris.",
    "section10Title": "10. Contact",
    "section10Content": "For any questions regarding these terms, contact us at: tom@dokal.life"
